We’ve been bombarded with social and commercial messaging throughout our lives that has made us terrified of weight gain and fixated on weight loss, all under the guise of health.
The adoration of slim bodies and phobia of weight gain, also known as fat-phobia , is essential to diet culture.
Admittedly, that degree of weight gain wasn’t healthy for me.
In my recovery, I finally released control, and that’s when I began to gain weight.
And so, whether or not you’re convinced of the potential risks of diet culture, all I ask is that you consider this one simple question: what if your weight didn’t matter?